{{distinguish|Duke of Arcos}} {{refimprove|date=July 2016}}
'''Duke of Arco''' is a [[List of dukedoms in Spain|Spanish noble title]]. It was created by King [[Philip V of Spain]] in 1715 for [[:es:Alonso Manrique de Lara y Silva|Alonso Manrique de Lara y Silva]].
==List of Dukes of Arco== {| class="wikitable" |- ! !! Title holder !! Period |- bgcolor="#dddddd" | ! colspan="3" | Created by [[Philip V of Spain]] |- | I || [[:es:Alonso Manrique de Lara y Silva|Alonso Manrique de Lara y Silva]] || 1715 ‚Äì 1737 |- | II || [[Lu√≠s Lasso de la Vega y Manrique de Lara]] || 1737 ‚Äì 1768 |- | III || [[Francisco Lasso de la Vega y Sarmiento]] || 1768 ‚Äì 1805 |- | IV || [[Mar√≠a Andrea Lasso de la Vega y Silva]] || 1805 ‚Äì 1806 |- | V || [[Mar√≠a Vicenta de Sol√≠s y Lasso de la Vega]] || 1806 ‚Äì 1840 |- | VI || [[Mar√≠a Pilar Osorio y Guti√©rrez de los R√≠os]] || 1840 ‚Äì 1921 |- | VII || [[Manuel Felipe Falc√≥ y Osorio]] || 1921 ‚Äì 1927 |- | VIII || [[Mercedes Falc√≥ y de Anchorena]] || 1927 ‚Äì present |- |}
===Succession=== As with other Spanish [[noble title]]s, the [[Duke|dukedom]] of Arco descended according to [[cognatic primogeniture]], meaning that females could inherit the title if they had no brothers (or if their brothers had no issue), such as in the 7th Duchess's case. The rules were relaxed in 2006, since when the eldest child (regardless of gender) can automatically succeed to noble [[hereditary title|family titles]].
The 7th Duchess married Fernando de Soto y Col√≥n de Carvajal (1930-2001), V Count of Puerto Hermoso, X Marquis of Arienzo, and it is expected that their son, Manuel de Soto y Falc√≥, will succeed to his mother's dukedom.<ref>[https://books.google.es/books?id=KRYMncjc2GUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=nobleza+espanola+inmemorial+1520&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjkwIKzzvrLAhVJtRoKHcqECmQQ6AEIHTAA#v=onepage&q=nobleza%20espanola%20inmemorial%201520&f=false ''Nobleza Espa√±ola Grandeza Inmemorial 1520'' (Madrid, 2009)]</ref>
