The '''Cold War''' ({{lang-ru|—Ö–æ–ª–æÃÅ–¥–Ω–∞—è –≤–æ–π–Ω–∞ÃÅ, kholodnaya voƒ≠na}}) was the global situation from around 1947 to 1991 of political conflict, military tension, [[Proxy War|proxy wars]], and propaganda campaigns between the [[Second World|Communist World]] ‚Äî primarily the [[Soviet Union]] and [[China]] and their [[satellite state]]s and allies ‚Äî and the powers of the [[Western world#The Cold War|Western world]], primarily the United States and its [[NATO|NATO allies]].
